Phenome-environment wide sex differences in NHANES¶

Toms Gonzlez Zarzar
12/20

Main purpose¶

To identify environmental exposures that have differential effects between sexes/genders

For example¶

Analysis plan¶

  • QC process using Clarite and following Nikki's plan
  • Based on previous research, meta-analyze the different cohorts (Winkler et al. 2017)
  • Normalize the variables to keep the $\beta$ coefficients consistent
  • Successive EWAS models with a different environment-phenotype pair, while controlling for covariates, stratified by sex
  • From those models that converged, compare the $\beta$ coefficients between sexes, using the following test:
$$ Z_{diff} = \frac{\beta_{1pq} - \beta_{2pq}}{\sqrt{se^2_{1pq} + se^2_{2pq}}} $$

Exploratory analyses¶

There are 390 variables, and 9847 females and 9090 males

From the 390 variables, 53 are phenotypes, 8 are covariates, and 329 are exposures

Preliminary results¶

After the analysis, there are 9362 total tests due to non-convergence in either sex
or because clarite couldn't estimate the effect sizes


There are 157 significant bonferroni corrected results, and 497 FDR < %5
